# UI Building Blocks — Dual-Platform NuDS Rule

## Scope

This rule applies to **Prototype screens** (UI Building Blocks) only:
- `screens/*Screen.tsx` → Expo Go (React Native)
- `web/src/screens/*Screen.tsx` → Web (Vite)

It does NOT apply to Platform pages (HomePage, GlossaryPage, ExperienceArchitecturePage, ProjectTimelinePage).

## Core Principle

Every UI Building Block change MUST be delivered to **both platforms** in the same task.
If you edit `screens/SimulationScreen.tsx`, you must also update `web/src/screens/SimulationScreen.tsx` (and vice-versa).

## Styling Hierarchy (NuDS-first)

Always resolve styling in this order. Move to the next level ONLY if the current one cannot express the need.

### Level 1 — NuDS Token (highest priority)
Use semantic tokens from the theme object for all colors, spacing, radius, typography, and elevation.

```
theme.color.main              // brand accent
theme.color.content.primary   // text
theme.color.content.secondary // secondary text
theme.color.positive           // success green
theme.color.negative           // error red
theme.color.warning            // attention orange
theme.color.background.screen  // page background
theme.color.background.secondary // subtle bg
theme.color.border.secondary   // dividers
theme.color.surface.accentSubtle // highlighted cards
theme.color.surface.success    // savings badge bg
theme.spacing[5]               // 20px
theme.radius.xl                // 24px
theme.radius.full              // pill (64px)
theme.typography.titleXSmall   // { fontFamily, fontSize: 20, lineHeight: 24 }
```

NEVER use hardcoded hex colors like `#0c7a3a`, `#D01D1C`, `#820AD1` in Building Block screens.

### Level 2 — NuDS Component
Use NuDS components before building custom UI:

| Need | Expo (RN) | Web |
|------|-----------|-----|
| Text | `<NText variant="titleXSmall">` | `<NText variant="titleXSmall" theme={t}>` |
| Badge | `<Badge color="success">` | `<Badge color="success" theme={t}>` |
| Button | `<Button variant="primary" expanded>` | `<Button variant="primary" expanded theme={t}>` |
| Bottom Sheet | `<BottomSheet visible onClose title showHandle>` | motion.div + `.nf-proto__sheet` CSS |
| Top Bar | `<TopBar variant="modal" title>` | `<TopBar variant="modal" title theme={t}>` |
| Box | `<Box surface="screen">` | `<Box surface="screen" theme={t}>` |

### Level 3 — BEM CSS Class (web only)
For interactive states and custom UI not covered by NuDS (hover, press, slider, keypad, calendar):
- Use classes from `web/src/styles/prototype.css` with namespace `.nf-proto__*`
- These classes reference NuDS tokens via CSS custom properties (`var(--nuds-*)`)

### Level 4 — Inline Style (lowest priority)
Only for:
- Motion-driven values (framer-motion `animate`, RN `Animated`)
- Conditional/dynamic values computed at runtime
- Layout that is unique to one instance

## Platform Equivalence Map

| Concept | Expo Go | Web |
|---------|---------|-----|
| Theme access | `const theme = useNuDSTheme()` | `const { nuds } = useTheme(); const t = nuds;` |
| Accent color | `theme.color.main` | `t.color.main` |
| Primary text | `theme.color.content.primary` | `t.color.content.primary` |
| Secondary text | `theme.color.content.secondary` | `t.color.content.secondary` |
| Positive (green) | `theme.color.positive` | `t.color.positive` |
| Negative (red) | `theme.color.negative` | `t.color.negative` |
| Background | `theme.color.background.screen` | `t.color.background.screen` |
| Border | `theme.color.border.secondary` | `t.color.border.secondary` |
| Surface accent | `theme.color.surface.accentSubtle` | `t.color.surface.accentSubtle` |
| Spacing 20px | `theme.spacing[5]` (RN number) | `t.spacing[5]` (used as `${t.spacing[5]}px` in CSS) |
| Radius 24px | `theme.radius.xl` | `t.radius.xl` |
| Elevation | `theme.elevation.level1` (RN shadow) | `boxShadow.level1` (CSS string) |
| Typography | `variant="titleXSmall"` on NText | `variant="titleXSmall"` on NText + `theme` prop |

## Screen Discoverability (MANDATORY when adding/renaming a Building Block)

Every new Building Block screen MUST be surfaced in **all** these places, or the
designer will never find it from the menu. Never ship a Building Block that is
only wired in `App.tsx` / `web/src/App.tsx` — it must be listed.

### Shared registry (drives both platforms)

1. [`shared/data/screenVariants.ts`](shared/data/screenVariants.ts)
   - Add the key to `SCREEN_BLOCK_ORDER` in the correct flow order.
   - Add the key to `READY_SCREENS` once the screen is implemented on BOTH
     platforms (never add to `READY_SCREENS` half-done).
   - Add a `SCREEN_BLOCK_META[key]` entry with `title`, `description`, `path`.
   - Attach the key to a pack in `PACKS` (`flow`, `system`, etc.) so it appears
     under the right group heading.

2. [`config/screens.registry.ts`](config/screens.registry.ts) — add an entry
   with `name`, `title`, `type`, `component`, `transition` (from
   `TransitionPresetName`), `description`, `status: 'done' | 'soon'`.

3. [`config/emulatorConfig.ts`](config/emulatorConfig.ts)
   - Add the key to `SCREEN_BLOCK_ORDER` (kept in sync with shared one).
   - Add the key to `SCREEN_VARIANTS_DEFAULTS`.
   - If the screen is optional (gated by a use case flag such as `pinEnabled`),
     extend `FlowOptionKey` + `buildInitialFlowOptionState()` accordingly.

### Expo (React Native) menus

4. [`screens/BuildingBlocksScreen.tsx`](screens/BuildingBlocksScreen.tsx)
   - Add the slug to `SCREEN_NAV_MAP` so `onNavigate` can route to it.
   - The list is auto-rendered from `SCREEN_BLOCK_ORDER` + `READY_SCREENS`, so
     once those are updated the card appears automatically — but verify by
     running Expo Go.

5. [`App.tsx`](App.tsx)
   - Add the screen to the `Screen` discriminated union.
   - Handle `case '<key>'` in `handleNavigate` + `renderScreen`.
   - Import the new screen component.

### Web menus

6. [`web/src/components/layout/ParameterPanel.tsx`](web/src/components/layout/ParameterPanel.tsx)
   - Add to the local `SCREEN_BLOCK_ORDER`, `READY_SCREENS`, `SCREEN_BLOCK_META`,
     `SCREEN_VARIANTS`, and `SCREEN_CONTENT_VARIANTS`.
   - Do NOT leave the key in `LEGACY_SCREENS` once the screen is shipped.

7. [`web/src/App.tsx`](web/src/App.tsx)
   - Add the key to `ScreenType`.
   - Add a branch in `resolveScreenType` mapping the URL slug to the key.
   - Add a render case that wires the screen inside the motion container.

8. [`web/src/components/layout/PrototypeViewport.tsx`](web/src/components/layout/PrototypeViewport.tsx)
   - Add the key to `EXPO_SCREENS` (if it exists on Expo).
   - Add metadata entry describing `components.web`, `components.expo`,
     `tokens`, `extensions`, `hardcoded`.

### i18n & docs

9. [`shared/i18n/types.ts`](shared/i18n/types.ts) — extend the `Translation`
   contract with any new copy keys.

10. [`shared/i18n/{pt-BR,en-US,es-MX,es-CO}.ts`](shared/i18n/pt-BR.ts) — add the
    new copy keys AND update the Building Blocks list entry from
    `status: 'soon'` to `status: 'done'` once ready.

11. [`web/src/data/projectTimeline.ts`](web/src/data/projectTimeline.ts) —
    flip the Jira task entry from `status: 'backlog'` to `status: 'done'`.

12. [`docs/UI-BUILDING-BLOCKS-GUIDE.md`](docs/UI-BUILDING-BLOCKS-GUIDE.md) —
    update the screen table (Expo path / Web path / Status).

If any of steps 1–8 is skipped, the screen is invisible to designers even if
the component file exists. Treat this list as the single source of truth when
reviewing a Building Block PR.

## Checklist (run mentally before completing any task)

- [ ] Are ALL colors from NuDS tokens? (no `#hex` literals)
- [ ] Are ALL text elements using `<NText variant="...">` or theme typography?
- [ ] Are ALL spacing values from `theme.spacing[N]`?
- [ ] Are ALL border-radius from `theme.radius.*`?
- [ ] Are bottom sheets using NuDS `<BottomSheet>` on Expo?
- [ ] Is the change delivered to BOTH platforms?
- [ ] Does the Web version use `nuds` from `useTheme()` (not just `palette`)?
- [ ] Does the Expo version import from `@nubank/nuds-vibecode-react-native`?
- [ ] Is the screen listed in `shared/data/screenVariants.ts` (order + ready + meta + pack)?
- [ ] Is the screen listed in `web/src/components/layout/ParameterPanel.tsx` (all 5 local maps) and REMOVED from `LEGACY_SCREENS`?
- [ ] Is the screen wired in `App.tsx` (Expo) AND `web/src/App.tsx` (Web) render switch?
- [ ] Did `i18n` and `projectTimeline` get flipped to `'done'`?

## File Locations

```
screens/                           → Expo Go screens
web/src/screens/                   → Web screens
web/src/nuds/                      → NuDS web adapter (NText, Badge, Button, TopBar, Box)
web/src/styles/prototype.css       → BEM extensions for web prototype screens
shared/data/                       → Shared data (glossary, screen variants)
config/                            → Shared business logic (calculator, formatters, use cases)
@nubank/nuds-vibecode-react-native → RN NuDS components (BottomSheet, Badge, Button, NText, TopBar)
@nubank/nuds-vibecode-tokens       → Design tokens (colors, spacing, radius, typography, elevation)
```
